%% RHODS Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
%% Source: architecture/rhoai-3.0/rhods-operator.md

sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Admin User
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant DSCICtrl as DSCI Controller
    participant DSCCtrl as DSC Controller
    participant CompCtrl as Component Controller
    participant Manifests as /opt/manifests/<br/>(kustomize)
    participant GwCtrl as Gateway Controller
    participant Envoy as data-science-gateway<br/>(Envoy) 443/TCP
    participant KAP as kube-auth-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OAuth as OpenShift OAuth<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Backend as Backend Service

    Note over Admin,K8sAPI: Flow 1: Platform Initialization
    Admin->>K8sAPI: Create DSCInitialization CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>DSCICtrl: Watch notification<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    DSCICtrl->>K8sAPI: Create namespace, NetworkPolicy<br/>TLS 1.2+
    DSCICtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Auth CR, Monitoring CR,<br/>GatewayConfig CR, HardwareProfile
    K8sAPI->>GwCtrl: Watch GatewayConfig CR

    Note over Admin,K8sAPI: Flow 2: Component Deployment
    Admin->>K8sAPI: Create/Update DataScienceCluster CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>DSCCtrl: Watch notification<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    DSCCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create component sub-CRDs<br/>(Dashboard, KServe, Ray, etc.)
    K8sAPI->>CompCtrl: Watch component CR
    CompCtrl->>Manifests: Render kustomize manifests
    Manifests-->>CompCtrl: Rendered K8s resources
    CompCtrl->>K8sAPI: Deploy manifests<br/>TLS 1.2+, ServiceAccount Token

    Note over Admin,OAuth: Flow 3: Gateway Setup
    GwCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create GatewayClass, Gateway<br/>EnvoyFilter, DestinationRule
    GwCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create kube-auth-proxy<br/>Deployment, Service, Secret
    GwCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create OAuthClient, HTTPRoute

    Note over Admin,Backend: Flow 4: Authenticated User Request (RHOAI 3.x)
    Admin->>Envoy: HTTPS Request<br/>443/TCP, TLS 1.2+<br/>Cookie / Bearer Token
    Envoy->>KAP: ext_authz check<br/>8443/TCP, HTTPS (service-CA)<br/>Cookie forwarding
    KAP->>OAuth: OAuth2 validation<br/>443/TCP, HTTPS, TLS 1.2+<br/>OAuth2 client credentials
    OAuth-->>KAP: Auth response
    KAP-->>Envoy: Auth result + identity
    Note over Envoy: Lua filter injects<br/>Bearer Token header
    Envoy->>Backend: Forward request<br/>via HTTPRoute<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (injected)
    Backend-->>Envoy: Response
    Envoy-->>Admin: HTTPS Response
